# Day 19: Biological Data Visualization
# Generates data/gwas.csv and data/expression_matrix.csv
#
# Data sources:
#   GWAS: Real loci from the NHGRI-EBI GWAS Catalog (Sollis et al.,
#     Nucleic Acids Res 51(D1):D1038-D1042, 2023). SNP IDs, chromosomal
#     positions (GRCh38), p-values, and trait associations are from actual
#     published GWAS. Studies include: GIANT height (Wood et al. 2014),
#     BMI (Locke et al. 2015), T2D (Mahajan et al. 2018), breast cancer
#     (Michailidou et al. 2017), Crohn's disease (de Lange et al. 2017),
#     schizophrenia (Trubetskoy et al. 2022), coronary artery disease
#     (van der Harst & Verweij 2018), LDL cholesterol (Willer et al. 2013).
#   Expression matrix: Representative tissue expression profiles modeled
#     on GTEx v8 (GTEx Consortium, Science 369:1318-1330, 2020). Gene
#     expression values (log2 TPM+1) for 40 genes across 8 tissues,
#     reflecting real tissue-specificity patterns from the GTEx portal.

print("Setting up Day 19: Biological Data Visualization")
print("Generating data files...")

# Create output directories
mkdir("data")
mkdir("figures")
mkdir("results")

# ── GWAS data: ~140 real loci from NHGRI-EBI GWAS Catalog ─────────────
